00:07:19.738 --> 00:07:25.588
up a younger member of the family to take over the business, rather than his own much older sons.

00:07:26.708 --> 00:07:32.138
Aldo was responsible for running Gucci in America, and he was instrumental

00:07:32.138 --> 00:07:35.945
in helping turn the business into an international powerhouse.

00:07:37.105 --> 00:07:40.765
Maurizio wouldn’t have to wait for long to re-enter the family business.

00:07:41.185 --> 00:07:47.035
In the same year as his wedding, Aldo invited him to New York to begin working for Gucci again.

00:07:47.905 --> 00:07:50.925
And life was good for the couple for a while.

00:07:51.635 --> 00:07:57.535
Professionally, business was booming, and Maurizio and Patrizia had become quite the pair.

00:07:58.205 --> 00:08:03.095
She was his right-hand woman, advising him on various Gucci business matters.

00:08:03.885 --> 00:08:09.525
The couple owned several properties, including the luxury New York penthouse that they lived in.

00:08:10.005 --> 00:08:14.455
Patrizia collected fine jewellery and Maurizio bought what

00:08:14.455 --> 00:08:18.075
was, at the time, the world’s largest wooden sailing boat.

00:08:19.285 --> 00:08:23.575
And they flaunted this wealth about town, driving around in a

00:08:23.755 --> 00:08:28.425
chauffeured car and entrenching themselves in New York’s social scene.

00:08:29.695 --> 00:08:33.325
They even reunited with Rodolfo Gucci, Maurizio’s

00:08:33.405 --> 00:08:37.165
father, after the birth of their first child in 1976.

00:08:38.144 --> 00:08:44.190
The reunion wouldn't last for long as just six years later, Rodolfo Gucci was dead.

00:08:45.220 --> 00:08:49.780
Upon his father’s death, Maurizio inherited his father’s Gucci shares,

00:08:50.050 --> 00:08:54.010
making him the majority shareholder of the iconic fashion house.

00:08:54.970 --> 00:08:58.130
And he wasn’t going to be a silent shareholder, either.

00:08:58.850 --> 00:09:01.940
While his father and uncle had always wanted to preserve

00:09:01.940 --> 00:09:06.090
Gucci as a family business, Maurizio had other plans.

00:09:06.860 --> 00:09:09.870
He didn’t like the direction the company had been heading.

00:09:10.510 --> 00:09:14.770
What he saw to be excessive franchising and mass production

00:09:14.770 --> 00:09:18.360
of products had degraded the brand’s name in his eyes.

00:09:18.900 --> 00:09:23.020
He wanted to bring exclusivity back to Gucci, even

00:09:23.040 --> 00:09:26.590
if he had to take his own family down in the process.

00:09:27.660 --> 00:09:32.170
His plan was to replace his uncle as Gucci’s president, its boss.

00:09:33.060 --> 00:09:38.031
To do this, he enlisted the help of his cousin, Paolo, Aldo’s son.

00:09:38.961 --> 00:09:44.110
Paolo had once been vice president of Gucci after years as chief designer.

00:09:44.740 --> 00:09:49.275
He is even credited as one of the minds behind the famous double G logo.

00:09:50.385 --> 00:09:54.555
However, he felt like his voice was not being heard enough.

00:09:55.185 --> 00:09:59.505
So, in 1980, he had gone behind his father’s back and

00:09:59.685 --> 00:10:03.545
opened his own, independent fashion line called Gucci Plus.

00:10:04.745 --> 00:10:07.885
When he found out, Aldo was furious.

00:10:08.325 --> 00:10:12.965
Not only did he fire his son, but he sued him for infringing

00:10:12.975 --> 00:10:16.235
Gucci trademarks and cut him off from its suppliers.

00:10:17.715 --> 00:10:22.050
Paolo wanted to seek revenge, and so the cousins made a deal.

00:10:23.130 --> 00:10:28.980
Paolo agreed to help vote Aldo off Gucci’s Board of Directors and in return,

00:10:29.310 --> 00:10:34.030
Maurizio would let Paolo independently lead some design work in the company.

00:10:35.540 --> 00:10:37.070
And the plan worked.

00:10:37.410 --> 00:10:40.580
Maurizio was able to take Aldo’s place as president.

00:10:41.530 --> 00:10:45.250
However, just as his professional life took off, his

00:10:45.280 --> 00:10:49.290
personal one was beginning to crumble, or at least, change.

00:10:50.678 --> 00:10:55.478
Despite their differences, just before his death, Rodolfo Gucci had warned

00:10:55.478 --> 00:11:00.848
Patrizia, his daughter in law, that Maurizio would change once he gained more power.

00:11:01.648 --> 00:11:04.978
“You will find you are married to another man,” he told her.

00:11:05.948 --> 00:11:07.908
And his prediction came true.

00:11:08.808 --> 00:11:14.138
Once he became president, Maurizio began spending less and less time with his family

00:11:14.408 --> 00:11:18.968
and started to cut Patrizia out of the day-to-day running of the Gucci business.

00:11:19.468 --> 00:11:22.998
She was no longer able to steer the company in her own direction.

00:11:24.132 --> 00:11:28.294
And it wasn’t just a lust for power that was driving Maurizio away.

00:11:29.304 --> 00:11:33.644
After buying his extraordinarily large sailing boat, he took a keen

00:11:33.664 --> 00:11:38.032
interest in sailing, sponsoring races and teams all over the world.

00:11:38.972 --> 00:11:44.264
And while Patrizia did not share this passion, he soon found someone who did.

00:11:45.384 --> 00:11:50.765
He met an American model called Sheree Loud at a sailing event in 1984.

00:11:51.674 --> 00:11:55.664
Despite both being married to other people, Maurizio avidly

00:11:55.664 --> 00:11:59.434
pursued her and the two began an affair that same year.

00:12:00.404 --> 00:12:03.074
They travelled together to sailing events across the

00:12:03.074 --> 00:12:05.824
world and Sheree helped him to renovate his boat.

00:12:06.494 --> 00:12:10.304
They seemed to have much more in common than Maurizio and Patrizia.

00:12:11.314 --> 00:12:17.354
And so, in March of 1985, Maurizio packed his bags and left his family home.

00:12:18.274 --> 00:12:22.374
At first, he told his wife that he was simply going on a business trip.

00:12:22.964 --> 00:12:29.134
But, the next day, he sent a mutual friend to tell her that he would not be returning at all.

00:12:30.394 --> 00:12:33.224
This, of course, greatly angered Patrizia.

00:12:33.954 --> 00:12:39.044
Not only did he not have the courage to tell her in person, but he also wanted her

00:12:39.074 --> 00:12:44.464
to keep up appearances and, in public, pretend that they were still happily married.

00:12:45.929 --> 00:12:49.639
The couple had not yet officially divorced, so Patrizia did

00:12:49.639 --> 00:12:53.379
as Maurizio asked, perhaps in the hopes of winning him back.

00:12:54.509 --> 00:12:58.799
Maurizio, meanwhile, was only able to enjoy his new life as the

00:12:58.799 --> 00:13:03.069
president of Gucci and free from his controlling wife for a short time.

00:13:04.579 --> 00:13:09.589
Aldo, his uncle, felt publicly humiliated by his exile from Gucci.

00:13:10.099 --> 00:13:15.569
His nephew had removed many aspects of the company that were considered his legacy.

00:13:16.609 --> 00:13:19.789
Paolo also was unhappy with his cousin, Maurizio.

00:13:20.369 --> 00:13:25.189
