00:13:26.719 --> 00:13:34.479
So Aldo and Paolo teamed up and together they claimed that Maurizio, in order to avoid inheritance

00:13:34.479 --> 00:13:40.819
tax, had forged his father’s signature on forms transferring him his late father’s shares.

00:13:42.289 --> 00:13:46.889
And when they reported this to the authorities, Maurizio was charged with the crime.

00:13:47.659 --> 00:13:50.509
Luckily for him, he managed to avoid prison.

00:13:51.079 --> 00:13:56.899
In an almost James Bond-like fashion, as police were coming to arrest him he received

00:13:56.919 --> 00:14:01.599
a warning from his lawyer and quickly jumped on a motorbike, fleeing to Switzerland.

00:14:02.909 --> 00:14:08.719
This is where he would stay for several years until he was acquitted, essentially found not guilty.

00:14:10.139 --> 00:14:13.349
During this time, he was stripped of the Gucci presidency.

00:14:13.679 --> 00:14:15.989
But, he still owned half of the company.

00:14:16.779 --> 00:14:21.829
Once again, he had to hatch a plan to, form a plan to regain control.

00:14:22.709 --> 00:14:26.209
